{
  "title": "AD #8 · Environmental Tax on Flights (Path C · Evaluate)",
  "lessons": [
    {
      "translation": "对机票征税听起来是个干净的点子——污染者付费，绿色科技获资金——但它是否真的有用，完全取决于税怎么设计。",
      "phrases": ["A tax on plane tickets", "sounds like a clean idea —", "polluters pay,", "green technology gets funded —", "but whether it actually helps", "depends fully on", "how the tax is designed."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "我只在很窄的形式下支持它：只对有火车替代的短途航线征，并法律规定税款必须进入清洁交通。",
      "phrases": ["I would support it", "only in a narrow form:", "place it on short routes", "where trains are already an option,", "and require by law", "that the money goes into", "cleaner transport."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "对每张票一刀切的税会在三个方面都失准。",
      "phrases": ["A flat tax on every ticket", "would miss the target", "on all three fronts."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "首先，方案只有在乘客能切换时才有效。",
      "phrases": ["First,", "the plan only works", "where passengers can switch."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "在巴黎—里昂或北京—天津这样的航线上，一点额外费用会把乘客推向高铁，真实排放下降。",
      "phrases": ["On routes", "like Paris–Lyon", "or Beijing–Tianjin,", "a small extra fee", "pushes travelers", "onto high-speed rail", "and real emissions drop."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "在长途航线上没有火车可选，同样的税只会变成固定成本。",
      "phrases": ["On long-haul flights,", "where no train exists,", "the same tax", "just becomes a fixed cost."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "航班照飞，账单落在经济舱乘客头上，而商务舱乘客由公司报销，毫无感觉。",
      "phrases": ["The flight still takes off,", "and the bill falls", "on economy passengers", "while business travelers,", "whose tickets are paid", "by the company,", "feel nothing."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "其次，规模太小。",
      "phrases": ["Second,", "the scale is too small."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "飞行占全球碳排约 2.5%；强制航司使用清洁燃料或加入更广的碳交易体系能覆盖更多。",
      "phrases": ["Flying makes up", "only about 2.5%", "of global carbon;", "forcing airlines", "to use cleaner fuel", "or join a wider carbon-trading system", "would cover far more ground."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "第三，在欧洲几次试点中，绿色税款被悄悄划入一般预算。",
      "phrases": ["Third,", "in several European trials,", "green-tax money", "was quietly moved", "into the general budget."]
    },
    {
      "translation": "没有法律锁定用途，这只是一个披着绿色标签的收入方案。",
      "phrases": ["Without legal rules", "locking the money to green use,", "this is a revenue plan", "with a green label."]
    }
  ]
}
